It&rsquo;s &ldquo;coldblooded&rdquo;
This is something that I did a while ago, so I thought I&rsquo;d just write a post about it. Here is a shell script to get every word that can be spelled with hexadecimal, sorted by length:
cat /usr/share/dict/words | tr &#34;[:upper:]&#34; &#34;[:lower:]&#34; | grep -E &#34;^[abcdeflzso]+$&#34; | tr &#34;lzso&#34; &#34;1250&#34; | awk &#39;{print length, &#34;0x&#34; $0}&#39; | sort -nr -k 1 | cut -d &#34; &#34; -f 2 If that seems incredibly cryptic to you, don&rsquo;t worry.
